ORGANIZATION: Contoso Health Plan (synthetic)
DEPARTMENT:   Claims Operations
DOCUMENT:     SOP-CLM-001 Rev 3
EFFECTIVE:    January 1, 2026

1. PURPOSE
----------
This document defines the standard operating procedures for
processing medical, pharmacy, and dental claims submitted to
Contoso Health Plan (synthetic). These procedures ensure
compliance with CMS regulations, state mandates, and NCQA
accreditation standards.

2. SCOPE
--------
Applies to all claims analysts, supervisors, and quality reviewers
within the Claims Operations department.

3. CLAIMS INTAKE PROCEDURES
------------------------------
  □ Verify claim receipt via EDI 837 (Professional/Institutional)
  □ Validate member eligibility at date of service
  □ Check provider network status (in-network vs. OON)
  □ Apply coordination of benefits (COB) rules if applicable
  □ Route to auto-adjudication engine or manual queue

4. AUTO-ADJUDICATION RULES
-----------------------------
  ┌──────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Rule Category             │ Description                         │
  ├──────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Duplicate Detection       │ Match by member + DOS + CPT + NPI  │
  │ Benefit Verification      │ Validate against plan benefit grid │
  │ Fee Schedule Application  │ Apply contracted or UCR rates      │
  │ Prior Authorization       │ Check auth requirements by CPT     │
  │ Bundling / Unbundling     │ Apply CCI/MUE edits               │
  │ Medical Necessity         │ Route to UM if criteria not met    │
  │ Timely Filing             │ 90-day clean claim window          │
  └──────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┘

5. MANUAL REVIEW TRIGGERS
-----------------------------
  • Claims > $10,000 (threshold review)
  • Out-of-network emergency claims
  • Claims with medical policy exceptions
  • Coordination of benefits conflicts
  • Provider dispute / resubmission
  • State mandate-specific services

6. PAYMENT PROCESSING
------------------------
  6.1 Generate Explanation of Benefits (EOB) per claim
  6.2 Process provider payment via EFT / check (835 remittance)
  6.3 Apply member cost-sharing (copay, coinsurance, deductible)
  6.4 Post payment to claims system within 3 business days
  6.5 Transmit 835 to clearinghouse for provider delivery

7. CLEAN CLAIM TURNAROUND STANDARDS
--------------------------------------
  ┌─────────────────────────────┬──────────────┐
  │ Claim Type                   │ Target (days) │
  ├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────┤
  │ Electronic clean claims      │ ≤ 14          │
  │ Paper clean claims           │ ≤ 30          │
  │ Non-clean claims (pended)    │ ≤ 45          │
  │ Appeals / grievances         │ ≤ 30          │
  └─────────────────────────────┴──────────────┘

8. QUALITY ASSURANCE
-----------------------
  • Random audit: 5% of auto-adjudicated claims monthly
  • Financial accuracy target: ≥ 99.0%
  • Procedural accuracy target: ≥ 97.0%
  • NCQA audit readiness documentation maintained

